Animals that had been vaccinated with profilin alone or with QCDC alone and infected with E. maxima displayed reduced body weight gains between 0 and 9 days post-infection compared with uninfected controls (P
 < 0.05) (Fig. 2
). In fact, the weight gains of the profilin-only (461.2 ± 13.4 g) and QCDC-only (457.6 ± 15.9 g) groups were identical to the PBS control group (410.4 ± 12.5 g). In contrast, animals immunized with profilin plus QCDC had significantly greater body weight gains (486.1 ± 13.9 g) compared with the PBS controls.

Fecal oocyst shedding was decreased in the profilin alone (1.46 ± 0.08 × 107) and profilin plus QCDC (1.22 ± 0.04 × 107) groups compared with the PBS control group (2.57 ± 0.24 × 107) and with the QCDC-only group (2.33 ± 0.13 × 107) (P
 < 0.05) (Fig. 3
). However, no difference in oocyst shedding was observed between the profilin alone and profilin plus QCDC groups.

The levels of mRNA transcripts encoding IL-1β, IL-15 and IFN-γ in the intestinal jejunum were increased in the profilin plus QCDC group compared with the PBS control, QCDC alone, and profilin alone groups (P
 < 0.05) (Fig. 4
).
